  'thumbnail_emoji' => '🌧',
  'is_premium' => 1,
  'is_published' => 1,
  'order' => 1,
  'summary' => 'Learn what depression actually is, why it is not a character flaw, and how it affects your brain and body.',
  'summary_sw' => 'Jifunze maana halisi ya unyogovu, kwa nini si udhaifu wa tabia, na jinsi unavyoathiri akili na mwili wako.',
  'content' => "## What is depression?\n\nDepression is not sadness. Sadness is a normal human response to loss or disappointment. Depression is a medical condition that affects how your brain processes emotion, motivation, and energy. It can arrive without an obvious reason, and it does not leave just because you try harder.\n\n## What is happening in your brain\n\nWhen you are depressed, the parts of your brain that regulate mood are working differently. Neurotransmitters like serotonin, dopamine, and noradrenaline are out of balance. This is not a personal failure. It is biology.\n\nYou may notice:\n- Persistent low mood most of the day\n- Loss of interest in things that used to matter\n- Fatigue even after sleep\n- Difficulty concentrating or making decisions\n- Negative thoughts that feel absolutely true\n- Changes in appetite or weight\n\n## The cruel trick of depression\n\nDepression lies to you. It says things like *Nothing will ever get better*, *I am a burden*, *There is no point*. These thoughts feel like facts. They are symptoms.\n\nOne of the most important things you can do is learn to notice when a thought is coming from your depression rather than from reality.\n\n## You are not your depression\n\nYou are a person experiencing depression. That distinction matters. Depression affects what you can do right now. It does not define who you are or what you are capable of.\n\n## What helps\n\nEvidence shows that these approaches reliably reduce depression:\n- Behavioural activation: doing small meaningful activities even when motivation is absent\n- Cognitive restructuring: challenging the distorted thoughts depression produces\n- Sleep hygiene: protecting the sleep that depression disrupts\n- Social connection: even brief, low-effort contact with others\n- Physical movement: exercise is as effective as medication for mild-to-moderate depression\n- Professional therapy: CBT and IPT have strong evidence bases",
  'content_sw' => "## Unyogovu ni nini?\n\nUnyogovu si huzuni. Huzuni ni jibu la kawaida la binadamu kwa kupoteza au kukatishwa tamaa. Unyogovu ni hali ya kiafya inayoathiri jinsi ubongo wako unavyoshughulikia hisia, motisha, na nguvu.\n\n## Kinachoendelea kwenye ubongo wako\n\nUnapoumwa na unyogovu, sehemu za ubongo wako zinazodhibiti hisia zinafanya kazi tofauti. Hii si kushindwa kwako binafsi, ni biolojia.\n\n## Unasaidiwaje\n\nUthibitisho unaonyesha kwamba hizi zinasaidia: shughuli za tabia, kurekebisha mawazo, usingizi mzuri, miunganiko ya kijamii, na mazoezi ya mwili.",
  'key_takeaways' => json_encode(["Depression is a medical condition, not a weakness or character flaw.", "Your brain chemistry changes during depression, this is not your fault.", "Negative thoughts in depression are symptoms, not facts.", "Multiple evidence-based approaches exist and work.", "You are not your depression, it is something you are experiencing."]),
  'key_takeaways_sw' => json_encode(["Unyogovu ni hali ya kiafya, si udhaifu.", "Mabadiliko ya kemikali ya ubongo wakati wa unyogovu si kosa lako.", "Mawazo mabaya katika unyogovu ni dalili, si ukweli."]),
