  'summary' => 'Depression wrecks sleep, and poor sleep worsens depression. Learn the evidence-based techniques to reclaim your rest.',
  'summary_sw' => 'Unyogovu unaharibu usingizi, na usingizi mbaya unazidisha unyogovu. Jifunza mbinu za kupata pumziko lako.',
  'content' => "## The sleep-depression cycle\n\nDepression disrupts sleep in two main ways: it either causes insomnia or hypersomnia. Both make the depression worse. Poor sleep reduces the brain's ability to regulate emotion, increases negative thinking, and kills motivation.\n\n## What actually works\n\n**Fix your wake time first.** Choose a consistent wake time and keep it even on weekends, even if you had a bad night. This anchors your circadian rhythm.\n\n**Get bright light in the morning.** Within 30 minutes of waking, expose yourself to bright natural light. This is the strongest signal your brain has to calibrate its clock and lift daytime mood.\n\n**Do not lie in bed awake.** If you cannot sleep after 20 minutes, get up and do something quiet. Return to bed when sleepy. This prevents your brain from associating bed with wakefulness and anxiety.\n\n**Cut the phone an hour before bed.** The blue light from screens suppresses melatonin. More importantly, checking social media activates the anxiety circuits you need to quiet.\n\n**Wind-down ritual.** A consistent ritual of 10 minutes, such as herbal tea, stretching, or gratitude notes, trains the nervous system to transition into sleep.\n\n**Limit daytime naps.** If you must nap, keep it to 20 minutes before 2pm.\n\n## For hypersomnia (sleeping too much)\n\nSleeping 12 to 16 hours does not mean you are getting more rest. In depression it usually increases fatigue and isolation. Use behavioural activation to create reasons to get up.",
  'content_sw' => "## Mzunguko wa usingizi na unyogovu\n\nUnyogovu huharibu usingizi, na usingizi mbaya huzidisha unyogovu. Mzunguko huu unaweza kuvunjwa.\n\n## Kinachofanya kazi kweli kweli\n\nWeka wakati wa kuamka mapema hata wikendi. Pata mwanga mkali asubuhi. Usikae kitandani ukiwa macho. Punguza simu saa moja kabla ya kulala. Fanya utaratibu wa kupumzika.",
  'key_takeaways' => json_encode(["Depression disrupts sleep both ways, insomnia and hypersomnia both worsen the condition.", "Fix your wake time first, it is the strongest lever for stabilising your sleep cycle.", "Morning bright light is the most powerful signal to calibrate your brain's clock.", "Do not lie in bed awake, get up after 20 minutes and return when sleepy.", "A consistent wind-down ritual trains your nervous system to transition to sleep."]),
  'key_takeaways_sw' => json_encode(["Weka wakati wa kuamka unaofanana kila siku.", "Mwanga wa asubuhi ni muhimu kwa mzunguko wako wa saa.", "Usikae kitandani ukiwa macho zaidi ya dakika 20."]),
